<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-e6fbd551289149dca63b50db037e95f587c0ccc3">The dual aspect of the Filthy Rag of the Wight</h2>
The Filthy Rag of the Wight is a guaranteed drop if you kill the Emporer Wight in the Wight quest at Bree. <p>
The Rag itself is created in one of two forms: 
</p>

    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
The Filthy Rag of the Wight [1,-1](40%) (+2 to searching) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
The Filthy Rag of the Wight [1,-1](+6) (+6 to searching) 
</p>
</li>

    </ol>


<p>
The first increases your mana capacity by 40%. The second increases your spell power by 6. You have an even chance of getting one or the other. 
</p>
<h2 id="head-6b58e13198628c8850c29648bb87329a17c458e8">The Filthy Rag of the Wight</h2>
It increases your intelligence and searching by 2. It increases your mana capacity by 40%, <em>or</em> your spell power by 6. It provides resistance to blindness and confusion. It renders you especially vulnerable to fire. It allows you to see invisible monsters. It cannot be harmed by acid, cold, lightning or fire. <h2 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h2>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I've enchanted up my Filthy Rag; I don't remember the base + to AC it came with... <p>
<a href="./SimonSorc">SimonSorc</a>: I think it starts at -1 but I'm not 100% sure. I do remember it was not good AC before I enchant it... 
</p>
